A Gateway to Training and Resources for Finite Element Analysis

FEA knowledge which will empower you

My name is Tony Abbey, and my passion is structural analysis. My mission is to share the knowledge and experience gained after over 40 years working in this field.

This FEA resource site provides you with the background and practical guidance needed to carry out your analyses with confidence.

It answers questions such as:

  • What theoretical background I need to understand the implications of my analysis?
  • What is best practice for this type of analysis?
  • What practical hints and tips do I need to be able to carry out analysis effectively?

Whether you are just starting to get to grips with FEA or are an experienced user – advice is always welcome. You will find plenty of that within this site.

The content

My FEA Articles and Software Reviews are available to all visitors

  • They include short 800 word opinion pieces through to 4000 word in-depth articles, heavily illustrated

Free FEA Training Course Material is available when you sign up

  • The courses are right here, they are video based and are rich with extra material, downloadable files etc.
  • They cover technical areas and a growing set of FEA solver specific tutorials
  • The material provides an important supplement to my existing live e-Learning classes
